title: High Adventure: Being an Account of the Adventures of a Printer-Cowboy on the "S.S. Occidental Victory" Which Encountered Storms in the North Atlantic and Shipwreck in the Baltic Sea While Carrying Horses to Poland and Sugar to Finland
description: Self-published autobiographical account of an eventful sea voyage bringing supplies to war-torn Europe. The second half of the book is poetry written by the author while shipwrecked.
author: John Wesley Clay
